description: Upon learning that a man received a suspended prison sentence for lighting his cigarette with the flame of the Unknown Soldier in Paris, urologist Bertrand Guillonneau remembered performing the same act in the 1980s after losing a bet.

headline: 'It is Jesus who speaks through me': The enigmatic life of Marthe Robin
description: 'Marthe Robin, Saint Or Fraud?' (1/5). In the 1920s, a paralyzed and bedridden farmer's daughter became a Catholic mystic known for her supernatural visions, and crowds flocked to see her until she died in 1981.

headline: AI, my students and me: 'Last semester marks the nadir of my experience in academia'
description: 'Letters from America' (1/6). The writer and journalist Thomas Chatterton Williams has been startled by the omnipresence of artificial intelligence at university, which he believes threatens the very foundations of education and our ability to think.

headline: Henri Matisse and his heirs: The end of a financial windfall
description: Since Henri Matisse's death in 1954, four generations of his family have guarded his vast body of work jealously and with the utmost discretion. But when the painter's work entered the public domain in January, it ended the lucrative reproduction rights the heirs had enjoyed, as well as their oversight of everything concerning their ancestor.

headline: China's robotics industry surges amid promise of a $5 trillion market
description: From a global conference to robotic games inside the National Stadium, Beijing becomes the world capital of robots from August 8 to 17. The event showcases China's extraordinary acceleration in this sector – from automated industrial arms to AI-powered humanoids.
